  "market_context": "Intraday session where price swept a prior high, broke structure downward, forming a bearish order block from the up-close candle that swept liquidity. Price later retraced to the OB open and was resisted.",
  "key_observation": "The analyst identified a bearish order block formed by the up-close candle that swept liquidity before breaking structure down; price later returned to the OB open and showed resistance there.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: The analyst confirmed price swept a prior high (buy-side liquidity) on the NQ 1-hour chart.",
    "Step 2: The analyst verified a break of structure downward occurred after the sweep, confirming a market structure shift.",
    "Step 3: The analyst identified the up-close candle that swept liquidity just before the structure break and marked its open as the bearish order block (OB).",
    "Step 4: The analyst observed price retracing back to the OB open level and being resisted there, confirming the OB as a supply zone."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "A valid bearish order block is formed by the up-close candle preceding a structure break after a liquidity sweep; price often returns to the OB open and respects it as resistance, providing high-probability short entries.",
